ice comet was class-defining when Vox and Nag were the end-game.  as soon as they added levels 51-60 and mobs that were almost completely resistant to all but lure spells, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> lures</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> became class-defining.  were guilds looking for wizards for ice comet after level 50?  nah, nope, negative.  we're how many expansions past the original game with the <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> mythical, all powerful</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> ice comet? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugrimstafftheurgist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimstaff Theurgist</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.kestrelarts.com/images/grimicon.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/8/02 7:03:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1029.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Ice Cometacious</span><hr size=1> You are missing the point.  What makes a spell class-defining isn't &quot;what guilds want for post 50 raids&quot; it is &quot;what do people consider the coolest aspect of the class&quot; and &quot;what do people refer to when they talk about the class' power.&quot;  This is NOT lure, it is Ice Comet.  It still is, and it probably always will be unless garrisons becomes a lot more common.<br>
<br>
The fact is, Ice Comet still is a benchmark.  As ANY pre-50 Wizard what spell they are working toward: Ice Comet, or any given Lure spell.  I'd be suprised if any of them - particularly wizards who are playing the class for the whole game, not just for x raids at y level - said anything but Ice Comet.  Now repeat this with anyone else, any non-Wizard.  Ice Comet is still the big cheese, even though its not the best spell any more.<br>
<br>
See you are basing your concept of what defines the class on what your guild wants a Wizard to be after level 50.  That's a pretty narrow slice of the game, you have to admit. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ukaziqueal.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kaziqueal</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/8/02 8:05:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1029.topic&index=24>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ice Cometacious</span><hr size=1> You are arguing perception, and everyone is going to have their own reasons for playing their classes. For me, class defining is our powerful ae's or perhaps banes. For others it's going to be manaburn, or crits. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uaurianne.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aurianne</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer<BR>I didn't like LOTR<BR>Blasphemer!!!</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/8/02 8:10:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1029.topic&index=25>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ice Cometacious</span><hr size=1> This is getting into an argument about what's considered &quot;class defining&quot; for a wizard. So I'm going to bring in the point I had as to why I believe this particular staff is fake, by quoting the first two paragraphs in my reply.<br>
